1
00:00:00,961 --> 00:00:02,212
<i>Previously on Riverdale...</i>

2
00:00:02,420 --> 00:00:04,631
They're ruining our lives,
and to them it's just a game.

3
00:00:04,839 --> 00:00:06,841
<i>They keep score
in some secret playbook.</i>

4
00:00:07,050 --> 00:00:08,718
You want vengeance?
I'm with you.

5
00:00:08,927 --> 00:00:11,471
- And I have a plan.
- You like shaming
people, Chuck?

6
00:00:11,680 --> 00:00:13,431
Apologize for ruining Polly.

7
00:00:13,640 --> 00:00:15,350
- What the hell?
- Do it, Jason!

8
00:00:15,558 --> 00:00:18,103
- Apologize for what
you did to me!
- Look, I'm not Jason!

9
00:00:19,604 --> 00:00:20,647
This is our insurance.

10
00:00:20,855 --> 00:00:23,400
Here, stash it. Keep it safe.

11
00:00:23,608 --> 00:00:25,652
Hermione Lodge will crumble.

12
00:00:25,860 --> 00:00:27,570
Maybe you should've sent her
to jail instead of Hiram.

13
00:00:27,779 --> 00:00:29,197
I heard
Mr. and Mrs. Blossom talking.

14
00:00:29,406 --> 00:00:31,074
<i>It sounded like
Clifford Blossom
was responsible</i>

15
00:00:31,282 --> 00:00:32,826
<i>for sending
Veronica's dad to jail.</i>

16
00:00:33,034 --> 00:00:34,494
Ever since we started
dating you've ignored me,

17
00:00:34,703 --> 00:00:36,204
- you've ditched me.
- Let me make it up to you.

18
00:00:36,413 --> 00:00:38,123
Sorry, Archie,
but I won't be bought.

19
00:00:38,331 --> 00:00:39,541
The lawyers
are coming over this week

20
00:00:39,749 --> 00:00:41,292
to take our statements
for your dad's hearing.

21
00:00:41,501 --> 00:00:42,585
Am I gonna have to lie?

22
00:00:42,794 --> 00:00:44,379
<i>My father is a criminal.</i>

23
00:00:49,259 --> 00:00:50,301
<i>Weekdays,</i>

24
00:00:50,510 --> 00:00:54,848
<i>from 8:25 a.m. to 3:01 p.m.,
we adhere to a strict regimen.</i>

25
00:00:55,181 --> 00:00:57,100
Everything in our
lives is controlled.

26
00:00:57,308 --> 00:01:00,020
<i>But then something
like the murder of
Jason Blossom happens,</i>

27
00:01:00,186 --> 00:01:03,398
<i>and you realize
there is no such thing
as control.</i>

28
00:01:03,606 --> 00:01:05,150
<i>There is only chaos.</i>

29
00:01:09,779 --> 00:01:14,409
<i>Nevertheless, some of us
strive to impose
and maintain order</i>

30
00:01:15,368 --> 00:01:18,371
<i>in what is, fundamentally,
an orderless world.</i>

31
00:01:20,999 --> 00:01:24,127
<i>A fact which would
very soon be confirmed</i>

32
00:01:25,295 --> 00:01:27,213
<i>in ways none of us
could have foreseen.</i>

33
00:01:33,303 --> 00:01:35,013
I'm, uh... I'm headed out.

34
00:01:35,221 --> 00:01:37,140
Sorry to be missing your
birthday this weekend, Jug.

35
00:01:37,348 --> 00:01:40,018
Oh, you will not be missing
anything, Mr. Andrews,

36
00:01:40,226 --> 00:01:42,062
I barely acknowledge
my own birthday.

37
00:01:44,189 --> 00:01:46,316
Arch, can you give me
a hand downstairs?

38
00:01:50,195 --> 00:01:53,448
The good news is that
all these divorce papers

39
00:01:53,656 --> 00:01:55,366
and legal mumbo jumbo
will be done.

40
00:01:55,575 --> 00:01:58,369
Should be behind us
by the end of the week.

41
00:01:58,578 --> 00:01:59,662
Are you only
going to see Mom now

42
00:01:59,871 --> 00:02:01,456
because you
and Hermione Lodge...

43
00:02:01,998 --> 00:02:04,459
No. No, son, I ended that.

44
00:02:05,085 --> 00:02:08,088
Being together,
working together,
not a good idea.

45
00:02:08,296 --> 00:02:09,339
In that case, then,

46
00:02:10,757 --> 00:02:13,927
why finalize things
in such a final way now?

47
00:02:14,135 --> 00:02:17,138
Sometimes, son, you just
gotta rip the Band-Aid off.

48
00:02:19,015 --> 00:02:20,391
Or you can try and fix things.

49
00:02:21,559 --> 00:02:23,228
We're past
that point, Archie.

50
00:02:23,436 --> 00:02:25,980
I spoke to Mom last week,
she didn't mention
any of this, Dad.

51
00:02:26,189 --> 00:02:28,316
Your mom moved out
two years ago.

52
00:02:29,109 --> 00:02:32,445
She didn't tell you
because she wanted me
to be the bearer of bad news.

53
00:02:33,863 --> 00:02:35,115
What if I came with you?

54
00:02:36,074 --> 00:02:37,492
This is between
me and your mom.

55
00:02:39,661 --> 00:02:40,703
I'll check in.

56
00:02:50,505 --> 00:02:51,381
What's going on?

57
00:02:51,589 --> 00:02:55,051
Veronica,
this is Paul Sowerberry,
your father's attorney.

58
00:02:55,260 --> 00:02:56,803
He's here to prep us
for our statements

59
00:02:57,011 --> 00:02:58,096
and help
at your dad's hearing.

60
00:02:58,304 --> 00:03:01,266
Except, I told you, Mom,
I'm not giving one.

61
00:03:01,474 --> 00:03:02,976
- Not one you'd want.
- Just...

62
00:03:03,184 --> 00:03:04,435
You won't be asked
any questions

63
00:03:04,644 --> 00:03:06,646
about your father's
business arrangements.

64
00:03:06,855 --> 00:03:08,982
We just need you
and your mother
to speak to his character.

65
00:03:09,190 --> 00:03:10,275
It'll humanize him.

66
00:03:10,483 --> 00:03:11,985
Which could mean
a lesser sentence.

67
00:03:12,193 --> 00:03:13,194
If you don't make a statement,

68
00:03:13,403 --> 00:03:15,530
well, that's problematic
and damaging.

69
00:03:15,738 --> 00:03:17,490
I've already told her
all of this.

70
00:03:17,699 --> 00:03:20,493
Well, Dad made his bed.
And I'm late for school.

71
00:03:21,661 --> 00:03:24,164
Veronica, there's something
we need to talk to you about.

72
00:03:24,372 --> 00:03:25,206
Bring it.

73
00:03:25,415 --> 00:03:27,709
After the morning I've had,
I'm ready for just about
anything.

74
00:03:27,917 --> 00:03:30,211
Okay, well, Archie
was with the Blossoms.

75
00:03:30,420 --> 00:03:33,423
While their Board
was in town, he, um...

76
00:03:34,757 --> 00:03:36,759
Why don't you tell her?
You were there.

77
00:03:38,136 --> 00:03:40,305
Why is this suddenly feeling
like a friendtervention?

78
00:03:40,513 --> 00:03:42,807
I overheard Mr. Blossom
say he's the one responsible

79
00:03:43,016 --> 00:03:45,268
for your dad being arrested
and put in jail.

80
00:03:47,687 --> 00:03:48,730
Are you kidding?

81
00:03:50,190 --> 00:03:51,357
Why the hell
would Clifford Blossom

82
00:03:51,566 --> 00:03:53,401
have anything to do
with why he's in prison?

83
00:03:56,821 --> 00:03:59,449
Hey, you may
or may not know this,

84
00:03:59,657 --> 00:04:02,744
but it's Jughead's birthday.

85
00:04:03,953 --> 00:04:06,331
What?
And he didn't say anything?

86
00:04:06,539 --> 00:04:09,000
It's tomorrow,
and he doesn't like
making a big deal out of it.

87
00:04:09,209 --> 00:04:11,377
Every year, he goes
to a double feature
at the Bijou.

88
00:04:11,586 --> 00:04:13,004
It's like this tradition.

89
00:04:13,713 --> 00:04:15,715
Last few years,
I've been his movie-buddy.

90
00:04:15,924 --> 00:04:16,799
But now
that he has a girlfriend...

91
00:04:17,008 --> 00:04:18,134
Well, of course,
I'll take him.

92
00:04:18,343 --> 00:04:19,469
But you should
still come with us.

93
00:04:19,677 --> 00:04:20,803
No. I don't wanna
be a third wheel.

94
00:04:21,012 --> 00:04:23,264
Come on.
It'll be like old times.

95
00:04:23,473 --> 00:04:24,724
The Three Musketeers.

96
00:04:25,516 --> 00:04:30,063
Actually, Archie,
there were four Musketeers.

97
00:04:30,271 --> 00:04:31,648
I'll see you later, Betty.

98
00:04:31,856 --> 00:04:32,774
Okay.

99
00:04:34,275 --> 00:04:35,526
<i>Yeah, this is Jones.</i>

100
00:04:35,735 --> 00:04:38,696
<i>Mr. Jones, hi,
this is Betty Cooper.</i>

101
00:04:38,905 --> 00:04:40,949
<i>- Jughead's...</i>
- Girlfriend, yeah, I remember.

102
00:04:41,157 --> 00:04:44,911
Great, well, I'm calling
because it's Jughead's
birthday tomorrow,

103
00:04:45,119 --> 00:04:47,664
and I wanted to see
if maybe you would come

104
00:04:47,872 --> 00:04:50,667
<i>see a movie with us,
maybe grab dinner?</i>

105
00:04:51,042 --> 00:04:52,293
Does he know
you're calling me?

106
00:04:52,502 --> 00:04:55,338
No, I thought
maybe I'd surprise him.

107
00:04:55,546 --> 00:04:57,382
Oh, man.

108
00:04:57,590 --> 00:04:59,259
There's one thing
that Jughead likes less

109
00:04:59,467 --> 00:05:01,302
than surprises,
and that's his birthday.

110
00:05:01,511 --> 00:05:03,513
Kid's never even had a party,
never wanted one...

111
00:05:03,721 --> 00:05:05,515
- What? Never?
<i>- Mmm-hmm.</i>

112
00:05:05,723 --> 00:05:09,352
Anyway, I think the best gift
that I could give to Jughead

113
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:10,520
would be to stay away.

114
00:05:10,728 --> 00:05:12,188
<i>But I appreciate
the call, Betty.</i>

115
00:05:12,897 --> 00:05:13,856
Okay.

116
00:05:16,067 --> 00:05:18,236
Anyway,
enough about my drama.

117
00:05:18,444 --> 00:05:20,571
Betty, you were saying
something about Jughead's
birthday?

118
00:05:20,780 --> 00:05:22,615
Yeah.
Just that Mr. Jones told me

119
00:05:22,824 --> 00:05:25,201
- Jughead's never had
a birthday party.
- Mmm-hmm.

120
00:05:26,202 --> 00:05:27,578
Let's have one for him.

121
00:05:27,787 --> 00:05:29,414
Like, a low-key
surprise party.

122
00:05:29,622 --> 00:05:31,708
- Uh, no, no.
- That's a fantastic idea.

123
00:05:31,916 --> 00:05:33,084
Jughead doesn't
like his birthday.

124
00:05:33,293 --> 00:05:34,502
Everybody says that,
nobody means it.

125
00:05:34,711 --> 00:05:35,753
Jughead is a lone wolf.

126
00:05:35,962 --> 00:05:37,672
Okay.
Ignoring the negativity.

127
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:38,965
Betty, you know me,

128
00:05:39,173 --> 00:05:41,426
- any excuse to wear
a cute party dress.
- Yeah.

129
00:05:41,634 --> 00:05:45,722
Okay, so I'm thinking
a quaint gathering,
inner-circle only.

130
00:05:45,930 --> 00:05:48,683
Oh, my God,
don't turn around.

131
00:06:00,403 --> 00:06:04,032
Holy Chuck,
I think his lats got bigger.

132
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,409
Not that I care,
because he's evil incarnate.

133
00:06:06,617 --> 00:06:07,785
What's Chuck Clayton
doing back?

134
00:06:07,994 --> 00:06:09,287
He got suspended,
not expelled.

135
00:06:09,495 --> 00:06:12,081
Even though he should
have been drawn and quartered
for what he did.

136
00:06:12,457 --> 00:06:13,124
Oh, my God.

137
00:06:14,167 --> 00:06:15,376
Get away from her, Chuck.

138
00:06:15,585 --> 00:06:19,130
Easy. Look, I only came
over here to apologize.

139
00:06:19,339 --> 00:06:20,631
You don't have to go
Dark Betty on me again.

140
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:22,008
I'm not going!

141
00:06:25,303 --> 00:06:26,888
I'm not going Dark anything.

142
00:06:28,473 --> 00:06:29,724
Ethel, is Chuck bothering you?

143
00:06:30,391 --> 00:06:31,934
You can relax,
Betty, it's fine.

144
00:06:32,977 --> 00:06:35,229
Yeah, Betty, we're fine.

145
00:06:35,938 --> 00:06:38,107
The real question is, are you?

146
00:06:53,539 --> 00:06:55,333
What was he doing?
Accosting her?

147
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:58,503
No, he was... Apologizing.

148
00:06:58,711 --> 00:06:59,962
Oh, I'm so sure.

149
00:07:00,171 --> 00:07:02,673
Chuck Clayton doesn't have
a contrite bone in his
muscle-bound body.

150
00:07:02,882 --> 00:07:04,550
You know what, can we talk
about something else?

151
00:07:04,759 --> 00:07:06,719
Like... Like Jughead's
surprise party.

152
00:07:10,890 --> 00:07:11,557
Betty?

153
00:07:14,185 --> 00:07:17,021
Look,
there's a lot I can't do,
a lot I can't control.

154
00:07:17,230 --> 00:07:18,189
But I can damn well make sure

155
00:07:18,398 --> 00:07:20,691
my boyfriend has the best
birthday of his life.

156
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:22,485
Screw it. I'm with Betty.

157
00:07:22,693 --> 00:07:24,278
My dad's away.
We can do it at my house.

158
00:07:24,487 --> 00:07:25,696
We could all use a good time.

159
00:07:25,905 --> 00:07:27,156
Now you're talking
my language.

160
00:07:28,116 --> 00:07:29,075
It's gonna be epic.

161
00:07:40,420 --> 00:07:41,629
Mr. Jones,

162
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:45,591
I didn't mean to ambush you.

163
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,969
I know you don't do birthdays,

164
00:07:48,177 --> 00:07:49,804
but Archie and I are having

165
00:07:50,012 --> 00:07:52,473
a few of Jughead's friends
over at Archie's house.

166
00:07:52,682 --> 00:07:56,978
And I bet it would mean
so much to Jughead
if you came.

167
00:07:57,145 --> 00:08:00,231
- Man, you don't quit, do you?
- Rarely, if ever.

168
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:02,233
I really wanna do
something special for him.

169
00:08:02,442 --> 00:08:03,818
And you being there...

170
00:08:04,777 --> 00:08:05,903
That would be special.

171
00:08:09,198 --> 00:08:10,283
Great news, Betty.

172
00:08:10,992 --> 00:08:13,703
I just had a terrific meeting
with Principal Weatherbee,

173
00:08:13,911 --> 00:08:15,705
who agrees
that the <i>Blue and Gold</i>

174
00:08:15,913 --> 00:08:18,249
can benefit greatly
from my professional guidance

175
00:08:18,458 --> 00:08:20,418
- as your new advisor.
- That's great, Mom.

176
00:08:20,626 --> 00:08:22,003
So what are we working on?

177
00:08:22,170 --> 00:08:24,797
A list of supplies
for Jughead's birthday party.

178
00:08:25,006 --> 00:08:27,467
You're really falling
for this Jones boy,
aren't you?

179
00:08:28,009 --> 00:08:30,970
Mom, when you and Dad
started dating,

180
00:08:31,179 --> 00:08:34,182
did you tell him everything

181
00:08:34,682 --> 00:08:36,017
about yourself?

182
00:08:36,225 --> 00:08:38,769
I sure did,
and I wish I hadn't.

183
00:08:38,978 --> 00:08:40,855
I shared things
with your father,

184
00:08:41,063 --> 00:08:44,317
my secrets, fears, doubts.

185
00:08:44,942 --> 00:08:46,360
And he ended up
using them against me.

186
00:08:46,569 --> 00:08:47,778
What secrets?

187
00:08:47,987 --> 00:08:49,614
Let's just say
that there are some things

188
00:08:49,822 --> 00:08:51,908
about myself that
I struggle with.

189
00:08:52,116 --> 00:08:53,784
I trust Jughead, Mom.

190
00:08:53,993 --> 00:08:56,996
Of course you do.
And you should.

191
00:08:57,538 --> 00:08:59,248
But just not with everything.

192
00:09:03,836 --> 00:09:07,048
So... A John Landis
double feature at the Bijou.

193
00:09:07,924 --> 00:09:10,384
<i>American Werewolf in London</i>
and <i>Animal House.</i>

194
00:09:10,551 --> 00:09:12,178
That's awesome. Except...

195
00:09:12,386 --> 00:09:13,638
You're going
with Betty instead.

196
00:09:13,846 --> 00:09:16,182
You told her
about my birthday?

197
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:18,559
Dude, come on.
That's a primal betrayal.

198
00:09:18,768 --> 00:09:20,269
Why do you hate
your birthday so much, Jug?

199
00:09:21,729 --> 00:09:23,314
PTSD from when I was a kid.

200
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:28,194
I don't know.
Things were always
messed up at home.

201
00:09:28,402 --> 00:09:29,570
Usually because of my dad.

202
00:09:29,779 --> 00:09:31,989
And then there was
this arbitrary day,

203
00:09:32,615 --> 00:09:35,868
that we would
just get together and
pretend things were great,

204
00:09:36,077 --> 00:09:37,620
we were normal.

205
00:09:38,579 --> 00:09:40,498
And it just made me feel
really lonely.

206
00:09:43,543 --> 00:09:44,544
What's all this?

207
00:09:44,752 --> 00:09:47,713
Dad's files
from the basement, Mom.

208
00:09:47,922 --> 00:09:49,340
Archie overheard Mr. Blossom

209
00:09:49,549 --> 00:09:50,675
say that he's the one
responsible

210
00:09:50,883 --> 00:09:52,009
for putting Dad in jail.

211
00:09:53,010 --> 00:09:54,387
So I did some digging.

212
00:09:54,595 --> 00:09:56,597
And found this spreadsheet
of monthly payments

213
00:09:56,806 --> 00:09:58,975
from Blossom Maple Farms
to Lodge Industries

214
00:09:59,183 --> 00:10:01,561
until about five months ago,
when they stopped.

215
00:10:02,436 --> 00:10:03,396
When your father was arrested.

216
00:10:03,604 --> 00:10:04,480
There's more.

217
00:10:04,689 --> 00:10:07,567
The payments,
which are significant,
by the way,

218
00:10:07,775 --> 00:10:10,027
have been happening
for 75 years.

219
00:10:10,236 --> 00:10:11,654
That's a ton of money.

220
00:10:11,862 --> 00:10:14,031
What if Clifford
implicated Daddy

221
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:15,700
to get out of paying
the monthly fee?

222
00:10:16,534 --> 00:10:18,244
I wouldn't put it past
the wig-wearing monster.

223
00:10:18,452 --> 00:10:20,162
- We should tell Dad's lawyers.
- Well, hold on.

224
00:10:20,371 --> 00:10:23,165
If Clifford did orchestrate
your father's arrest,

225
00:10:23,374 --> 00:10:25,042
people might think
that Hiram had something to do

226
00:10:25,251 --> 00:10:26,377
with Jason Blossom's murder.

227
00:10:26,794 --> 00:10:28,045
Ronnie?

228
00:10:28,254 --> 00:10:29,422
You got to let this go.

229
00:10:29,630 --> 00:10:30,631
You don't think Dad could,
in any way,

230
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:33,926
be responsible for Jason's
murder, do you?

231
00:10:34,135 --> 00:10:36,012
No, honey, look,
don't make things worse

232
00:10:36,220 --> 00:10:38,556
by asking questions
that no one else is asking.

233
00:10:39,181 --> 00:10:42,310
And please, God, do not
bring the Blossoms into this.

234
00:10:42,518 --> 00:10:43,561
And that includes Cheryl.

235
00:10:45,313 --> 00:10:49,150
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

236
00:10:49,358 --> 00:10:51,944
One, two, three, four... Stop.

237
00:10:54,864 --> 00:10:56,073
You're late, Veronica,

238
00:10:56,282 --> 00:10:58,409
we've already reviewed
the new choreography
for Homecoming.

239
00:10:58,618 --> 00:10:59,744
That means
you'll be in the back,
where your presence

240
00:10:59,952 --> 00:11:01,120
will do the least
amount of damage.

241
00:11:01,329 --> 00:11:02,622
With you front and center,
no doubt.

242
