485
00:26:01,895 --> 00:26:03,063
You're a straight-A student,

486
00:26:03,230 --> 00:26:06,149
you're a cheerleader,
for God's sakes.

487
00:26:06,358 --> 00:26:08,401
You're the perfect
girl next door.

488
00:26:08,610 --> 00:26:09,486
I hate that word.

489
00:26:09,694 --> 00:26:12,322
I'm the damaged loner outsider

490
00:26:12,531 --> 00:26:14,366
from the wrong side
of the tracks.

491
00:26:14,908 --> 00:26:17,285
Betty, come on.

492
00:26:17,494 --> 00:26:18,620
Who are we kidding?

493
00:26:20,413 --> 00:26:21,915
We're on borrowed time.

494
00:26:22,123 --> 00:26:23,333
What the hell
is that supposed to mean?

495
00:26:23,542 --> 00:26:27,295
Betty, I'm not one
of your projects, okay?

496
00:26:27,504 --> 00:26:28,922
Like solving Jason's murder...

497
00:26:29,130 --> 00:26:31,174
No. You're not a project,
you're my boyfriend.

498
00:26:31,383 --> 00:26:33,760
Until you're sick
of slumming it with me,

499
00:26:33,969 --> 00:26:35,720
or until Archie
changes his mind

500
00:26:35,929 --> 00:26:37,347
and says he wants
to be with you?

501
00:26:50,944 --> 00:26:52,404
Valerie, hey...

502
00:26:52,612 --> 00:26:54,489
- I'm looking for Melody.
- No, no, no, can we talk?

503
00:26:54,698 --> 00:26:56,825
I just wanted to say
what if... What if we made
a mistake?

504
00:26:57,033 --> 00:26:59,578
First of all,
we didn't do anything.

505
00:26:59,786 --> 00:27:01,830
I broke up with you
because I thought
you were a hot mess.

506
00:27:02,789 --> 00:27:03,748
Clearly, I was right.

507
00:27:04,958 --> 00:27:06,501
Wait, Valerie...

508
00:27:06,710 --> 00:27:08,253
What is your problem, Archie?

509
00:27:08,461 --> 00:27:10,255
You shut me out, remember?

510
00:27:10,463 --> 00:27:11,381
It's too late.

511
00:27:41,244 --> 00:27:43,538
<i>Archie,
everything all right?</i>

512
00:27:48,793 --> 00:27:50,545
- Jughead. Hey.
- Hey, Ethel.

513
00:27:50,754 --> 00:27:53,923
You didn't have
a piece of cake.
It's bad luck.

514
00:27:54,132 --> 00:27:55,967
This whole night
is bad luck.

515
00:27:57,969 --> 00:27:59,512
I'm ghosting.
I'll see you at school.

516
00:28:05,018 --> 00:28:06,019
Hey. Whoa.

517
00:28:06,227 --> 00:28:07,312
Where you going,
guest of honor?

518
00:28:08,980 --> 00:28:10,148
Get out of my way, Chuck.

519
00:28:10,357 --> 00:28:11,650
Oh, but you can't leave now.

520
00:28:13,360 --> 00:28:14,653
We haven't even
played our game yet.

521
00:28:15,862 --> 00:28:17,113
Listen up, party people.

522
00:28:18,531 --> 00:28:20,408
Everyone has their secrets.

523
00:28:20,617 --> 00:28:22,118
And we've all done
our fair share of sinning.

524
00:28:22,327 --> 00:28:24,496
That's one thing my dear
brother's death has revealed.

525
00:28:25,413 --> 00:28:27,832
So let's play a little game
to get those secrets
out in the open.

526
00:28:37,133 --> 00:28:39,135
What the hell
is Secrets and Sins?

527
00:28:39,344 --> 00:28:41,012
It's a variation
on Truth or Dare.

528
00:28:41,221 --> 00:28:43,723
In which we own our truths.

529
00:28:43,932 --> 00:28:45,141
By telling it like it is.

530
00:28:45,350 --> 00:28:47,852
I'll start the game
with Veronica Lodge.

531
00:28:48,061 --> 00:28:49,229
- Naturally.
- Let's begin

532
00:28:49,437 --> 00:28:51,648
with the day you and your
mob wife of a mother

533
00:28:51,856 --> 00:28:54,025
came to town
for a so-called "fresh start."

534
00:28:54,234 --> 00:28:55,735
Tell us, Veronica,
what's so fresh

535
00:28:55,944 --> 00:28:57,904
about defiling Archie Andrews
in a closet?

536
00:28:58,113 --> 00:28:59,739
- That was your doing.
- Moving on

537
00:28:59,948 --> 00:29:01,241
to dear Daddy Lodge...

538
00:29:01,449 --> 00:29:04,285
Isn't it true
that your father, from prison,

539
00:29:04,494 --> 00:29:06,579
illegally purchased
the drive-in land?

540
00:29:06,746 --> 00:29:07,997
Which makes me wonder.

541
00:29:08,206 --> 00:29:09,666
What else is he doing
from behind bars?

542
00:29:09,874 --> 00:29:11,543
Well,
I can't speak for my father,

543
00:29:11,751 --> 00:29:14,879
but I can think of someone
with a very dirty secret.

544
00:29:15,088 --> 00:29:18,007
Specifically, Cheryl killing
her very own brother.

545
00:29:18,216 --> 00:29:19,884
Everyone knows how much
I loved my brother.

546
00:29:20,093 --> 00:29:20,969
Exactly.

547
00:29:22,011 --> 00:29:23,388
But did you love him maybe

548
00:29:23,596 --> 00:29:25,682
in ways that a sister
shouldn't love a brother?

549
00:29:25,890 --> 00:29:29,978
And as you got older,
Jason started to think
it was strange, unnatural.

550
00:29:30,186 --> 00:29:32,272
So he chose Polly over you.

551
00:29:32,480 --> 00:29:33,940
So you shot him
between the eyes

552
00:29:34,149 --> 00:29:36,276
with one of your father's
many hunting rifles.

553
00:29:36,484 --> 00:29:39,195
This is riveting,
I can't breathe.

554
00:29:39,779 --> 00:29:40,905
This game is sick.

555
00:29:41,656 --> 00:29:44,033
- I wanna go next.
- That's the spirit, Doiley.

556
00:29:44,242 --> 00:29:46,035
What secrets do you have
to reveal to us?

557
00:29:46,244 --> 00:29:48,288
I saw Ms. Grundy's car

558
00:29:48,455 --> 00:29:51,207
by Sweetwater River,
the day Jason went missing.

559
00:29:51,416 --> 00:29:53,168
I told Betty and Jughead,

560
00:29:53,376 --> 00:29:54,919
and then,
Ms. Grundy quit her job

561
00:29:55,128 --> 00:29:57,380
and left Riverdale,
like, two days later.

562
00:29:57,589 --> 00:30:01,301
And let's not forget
that Archie was also at the
Sweetwater that morning.

563
00:30:01,509 --> 00:30:03,803
Oh, my God, color me shocked,
Archie Andrews.

564
00:30:04,012 --> 00:30:06,765
Is that why you became
a mediocre musician overnight?

565
00:30:06,973 --> 00:30:09,476
Because you and Ms. Foureyes
were pulling a Mary Kay
Letourneau?

566
00:30:09,684 --> 00:30:10,810
Don't say anything, Archie.

567
00:30:11,019 --> 00:30:12,270
Don't get in the gutter
with them.

568
00:30:12,479 --> 00:30:14,773
Wait, what?
Andrews was banging a teacher?

569
00:30:14,981 --> 00:30:16,399
Well, damn,
I wish I would have known.

570
00:30:16,608 --> 00:30:18,735
I would've added you
and Ms. Grundy to the
board of conquests.

571
00:30:18,943 --> 00:30:20,653
Classy, Chuck, as always.

572
00:30:20,862 --> 00:30:22,822
Wait a second,
that also explains

573
00:30:23,031 --> 00:30:25,325
why Archie can't seem to keep
a girlfriend to save his life.

574
00:30:25,533 --> 00:30:27,702
He's got serious
Mommy issues.

575
00:30:27,911 --> 00:30:29,662
Anything to say for yourself,
Arch?

576
00:30:29,871 --> 00:30:31,498
Were you victim
or perpetrator?

577
00:30:31,706 --> 00:30:33,166
Dilton Doiley plays with guns.

578
00:30:33,374 --> 00:30:34,125
Big whoop, Betty.

579
00:30:34,334 --> 00:30:37,170
So Doiley's a psychopath,
everyone knows that.

580
00:30:37,378 --> 00:30:39,130
Well, I guess
it's my turn now.

581
00:30:39,339 --> 00:30:43,343
Boy, do I have
a twisted secret to reveal.

582
00:30:43,510 --> 00:30:45,136
Starring Betty Cooper.

583
00:30:45,345 --> 00:30:46,346
Leave her
the hell alone, Chuck.

584
00:30:46,554 --> 00:30:47,722
Shut up, Andrews.

585
00:30:47,931 --> 00:30:49,933
Look, you may get a free
peepshow every night,

586
00:30:50,141 --> 00:30:51,309
but you do not know her.

587
00:30:51,976 --> 00:30:54,020
Hell, Betty doesn't
even know herself.

588
00:30:54,229 --> 00:30:56,022
Everybody knows
why I got suspended.

589
00:30:56,231 --> 00:30:58,191
But what you don't know...

590
00:30:58,399 --> 00:31:03,363
She dressed up like a hooker,
in a God-awful black wig,

591
00:31:03,530 --> 00:31:06,241
drugged me,
handcuffed me in the Jacuzzi,

592
00:31:06,449 --> 00:31:08,034
and I almost drowned

593
00:31:08,243 --> 00:31:10,870
until she got me to say
what she wanted to hear.

594
00:31:11,079 --> 00:31:13,206
And then she really lost it.

595
00:31:13,414 --> 00:31:15,416
She actually thought
she was Polly.

596
00:31:15,625 --> 00:31:18,044
But, hey, you knew
all about this, right,
Jughead?

597
00:31:22,674 --> 00:31:23,967
Enough! That's enough!

598
00:31:24,175 --> 00:31:25,552
Get your hands
off me, snake.

599
00:31:26,553 --> 00:31:27,554
Get out!

600
00:31:30,974 --> 00:31:32,016
Go on!

601
00:31:41,359 --> 00:31:43,570
What are you looking at?
The party's done.

602
00:31:45,363 --> 00:31:46,865
It's over! Go home!

603
00:31:51,578 --> 00:31:53,162
Whoa, where the hell
are you going?

604
00:31:53,371 --> 00:31:56,708
What, you want to give me
some advice on my right hook?

605
00:31:56,916 --> 00:31:58,626
I want you to go back inside
and talk to your girl.

606
00:31:58,835 --> 00:32:00,044
I don't think
it's gonna work out.

607
00:32:01,462 --> 00:32:03,256
Irreconcilable differences.

608
00:32:03,464 --> 00:32:06,467
Don't run away from it.
Don't run away.

609
00:32:06,676 --> 00:32:08,303
You've got something
good here.

610
00:32:08,511 --> 00:32:09,929
With her, with your friends.

611
00:32:10,138 --> 00:32:11,347
Something that...

612
00:32:11,556 --> 00:32:12,891
Something that we could
never give you.

613
00:32:14,475 --> 00:32:16,019
Also, man up.

614
00:32:16,227 --> 00:32:18,354
After what I just saw
in there, she needs you.

615
00:32:30,700 --> 00:32:32,619
FP.

616
00:32:32,827 --> 00:32:34,495
As block captain
of the Neighborhood Watch,

617
00:32:34,704 --> 00:32:35,914
I am obligated to ask you

618
00:32:36,122 --> 00:32:37,582
what you're doing
on this side of town.

619
00:32:37,790 --> 00:32:39,918
Don't act so high
and mighty, Alice.

620
00:32:40,126 --> 00:32:42,545
You may not live
on the Southside anymore,

621
00:32:42,754 --> 00:32:45,089
you may not dress like
you're from the Southside,

622
00:32:45,298 --> 00:32:47,133
but we both know the truth.

623
00:32:47,842 --> 00:32:49,594
Snakes don't shed
their skin so easily.

624
00:32:50,762 --> 00:32:51,930
Good night, FP.

625
00:32:52,138 --> 00:32:53,556
Now get the hell
out of my neighborhood.

626
00:32:53,765 --> 00:32:55,058
You're still hot, Alice.

627
00:32:55,266 --> 00:32:56,726
Too bad you're a stick
in the mud.

628
00:33:03,650 --> 00:33:06,361
And all this time,
I thought you were a lover,
not a fighter.

629
00:33:07,737 --> 00:33:08,738
I'm both.

630
00:33:09,572 --> 00:33:10,740
I've got layers.

631
00:33:12,951 --> 00:33:14,744
You were doing something nice,

632
00:33:15,328 --> 00:33:16,871
it's just that sometimes,

633
00:33:18,122 --> 00:33:20,875
when people do
nice things for me,
I short circuit.

634
00:33:21,084 --> 00:33:22,418
Maybe I'm not used to it.

635
00:33:22,627 --> 00:33:23,795
Maybe I'm scared.

636
00:33:26,005 --> 00:33:27,298
Of getting hurt.

637
00:33:28,132 --> 00:33:31,886
Or being rejected
for being myself.

638
00:33:34,514 --> 00:33:36,391
I should have told you
about Chuck.

639
00:33:38,017 --> 00:33:39,018
But I lied.

640
00:33:40,311 --> 00:33:44,524
And instead I threw you
this party that you
didn't even want.

641
00:33:46,025 --> 00:33:47,110
Why did you?

642
00:33:48,987 --> 00:33:53,700
Something is very,
very wrong with me.

643
00:33:54,450 --> 00:33:56,869
Like there's
this darkness in me

644
00:33:57,036 --> 00:33:59,330
that's overwhelming
sometimes,

645
00:33:59,539 --> 00:34:01,708
and I don't know
where it comes from.

646
00:34:01,916 --> 00:34:05,336
But I think that's what makes
me do these crazy things.
Like...

647
00:34:41,039 --> 00:34:43,541
How am I ever
gonna look anyone
in the eye ever again?

648
00:34:43,750 --> 00:34:45,960
By Monday,
this will all be but a dream.

649
00:34:46,961 --> 00:34:49,505
Trust me.
No one will remember anything.

650
00:34:49,714 --> 00:34:52,175
Except maybe that I accused
Cheryl of twincest.

651
00:34:56,262 --> 00:34:57,889
I drunk-dialed my dad, Ronnie.

652
00:34:58,097 --> 00:34:59,057
Archie.

653
00:35:00,767 --> 00:35:01,976
What did you say?

654
00:35:02,852 --> 00:35:04,896
I told him not to sign
the divorce papers.

655
00:35:06,189 --> 00:35:07,190
I don't even know why,

656
00:35:07,398 --> 00:35:09,067
it's not like I even want them
to get back together.

657
00:35:11,444 --> 00:35:13,279
Veronica,
why do I keep doing this?

658
00:35:13,488 --> 00:35:14,864
I keep wrecking things.

659
00:35:15,073 --> 00:35:16,240
Welcome to my life.

660
00:35:17,825 --> 00:35:21,162
Every day, I feel
like there's a new secret,

661
00:35:21,370 --> 00:35:23,247
a new lie
about my parents

662
00:35:23,456 --> 00:35:24,415
and what they've done.

663
00:35:27,293 --> 00:35:29,587
I don't want
my mom to be guilty, Archie.

664
00:35:30,713 --> 00:35:32,673
I really want that
to be a lie.

665
00:35:35,301 --> 00:35:36,427
Do you ever wonder...

666
00:35:38,513 --> 00:35:39,972
What if you had
done things differently,

667
00:35:40,181 --> 00:35:42,308
what if you had made
different choices?

668
00:35:42,517 --> 00:35:43,893
What do you mean,
different choices?

669
00:35:44,102 --> 00:35:45,436
Every day I wonder,

670
00:35:45,645 --> 00:35:47,772
what if I had left Riverdale
with my mom?

671
00:35:47,980 --> 00:35:48,940
Would things be...

672
00:35:50,650 --> 00:35:51,984
Would I be better off?

673
00:35:52,151 --> 00:35:54,237
I can't answer that, Archie,

674
00:35:54,445 --> 00:35:55,947
but we wouldn't have met,

675
00:35:56,155 --> 00:36:00,118
and that would've been
a tragedy of epic proportions.

676
00:36:02,328 --> 00:36:03,830
I'm messed up, Veronica...

677
00:36:04,038 --> 00:36:05,456
We all are, Archie.

678
00:36:06,749 --> 00:36:09,210
And, honestly,
you less than most.

679
00:37:34,712 --> 00:37:37,006
Veronica. Hey, good morning.

680
00:37:40,885 --> 00:37:42,553
Morning, Jughead.

681
00:37:46,224 --> 00:37:47,642
Um...

682
00:37:47,850 --> 00:37:48,726
So listen...

683
00:37:48,935 --> 00:37:52,063
Don't... Don't worry,
my lips are sealed.

684
00:37:52,647 --> 00:37:54,857
Okay. Cool.

685
00:37:57,735 --> 00:38:01,697
Smithers, you've known
my parents a very long time,
haven't you?

686
00:38:01,906 --> 00:38:04,242
Oh, my, yes, ages.

687
00:38:04,450 --> 00:38:09,163
And would you describe
my father as a good man?

688
00:38:10,456 --> 00:38:11,666
I'd rather not say, miss.

689
00:38:14,252 --> 00:38:16,379
And my mother, is she...

690
00:38:16,587 --> 00:38:18,130
Unequivocally good.

691
00:38:19,715 --> 00:38:21,133
No doubt in my mind
about that.

692
00:38:21,884 --> 00:38:23,010
Thank you, Smithers.

693
00:38:27,807 --> 00:38:30,518
- Veronica.
- I'm sorry I'm late.

694
00:38:32,979 --> 00:38:36,774
And thank you, Mom,
for not getting mad
that I slept over at Betty's.

695
00:38:37,775 --> 00:38:39,402
Thank you for coming.

696
00:38:39,610 --> 00:38:41,320
I believe in you, Mom.

697
00:38:46,367 --> 00:38:48,869
And I'm ready to go on record

698
00:38:49,078 --> 00:38:50,871
about how much
my mom and dad love me.

699
00:38:57,628 --> 00:38:59,672
Long night's journey into day?

700
00:39:05,011 --> 00:39:06,679
I can't face the music
right now.

701
00:39:06,887 --> 00:39:08,389
Yeah, I understand.

702
00:39:10,099 --> 00:39:11,600
So, you and Veronica...

703
00:39:13,769 --> 00:39:14,729
Yeah...

704
00:39:15,604 --> 00:39:17,273
- Jug...
- Don't worry.

705
00:39:17,481 --> 00:39:20,067
I'm never telling anyone
anything literally ever.

706
00:39:20,276 --> 00:39:21,277
Okay, good.

707
00:39:22,778 --> 00:39:24,280
Thanks. That's great.

708
00:39:30,953 --> 00:39:32,163
I brewed some High Point

709
00:39:32,371 --> 00:39:35,249
and brought you some aspirin
for the headache
I'm sure you have.

710
00:39:35,458 --> 00:39:36,500
Thanks, Mom.

711
00:39:39,378 --> 00:39:41,797
So I saw that you
invited Jughead's dad

712
00:39:42,006 --> 00:39:44,175
to your little
soiree last night.

713
00:39:44,383 --> 00:39:47,303
I did.
I thought it would be nice.

714
00:39:47,511 --> 00:39:51,140
And he was talking
to a long-haired delinquent
wearing a leather jacket.

715
00:39:51,349 --> 00:39:52,933
- You mean Joaquin?
- Is that his name?

716
00:39:53,142 --> 00:39:55,394
They know each other
through the Serpents.

717
00:39:55,603 --> 00:39:56,812
He's kind of dating Kevin.

718
00:39:57,021 --> 00:39:57,813
What?

719
00:39:58,564 --> 00:40:01,609
A Southside Serpent
dating the Sheriff's son?

720
00:40:02,943 --> 00:40:05,654
This is a small town,
but it's not that small.

721
00:40:11,327 --> 00:40:12,411
Hi there.

722
00:40:12,953 --> 00:40:17,166
Decaf skim latte
and a fresh scone.

723
00:40:17,875 --> 00:40:19,668
The last time
you brought me baked goods

724
00:40:19,877 --> 00:40:21,420
was because you kissed Archie.

725
00:40:26,884 --> 00:40:27,885
Betty...

726
00:40:28,761 --> 00:40:31,722
I just testified
on my father's behalf

727
00:40:31,931 --> 00:40:34,892
and helped his chances
of going free.

728
00:40:35,101 --> 00:40:37,144
That's good news, right?

729
00:40:38,354 --> 00:40:43,442
My dad hired Jughead's dad
to trash the drive-in.

730
00:40:43,651 --> 00:40:46,612
And given recent events,
it's not inconceivable

731
00:40:46,821 --> 00:40:50,408
that he might've hired him
to do other jobs.

732
00:40:51,409 --> 00:40:55,496
Like go after Jason
as payback for what
the Blossoms did to him.

733
00:40:59,708 --> 00:41:02,253
I want to help
with your investigation.

734
00:41:03,546 --> 00:41:04,630
I want the truth.

735
00:41:05,881 --> 00:41:06,882
Whatever it is.

736
